==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sensuous
<hw>Sen"su*ous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Of or
pertaining to the senses, or sensible objects; addressing the senses;
suggesting pictures or images of sense.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>To this poetry would be made precedent, as being less subtle and
fine, but more simple, <qex>sensuous</qex>, and passionate.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Highly susceptible to influence through the
senses.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Sen"su*ous*ly</wf> <pr>(#)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Sen"su*ous*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sent</ent>⟦br⟧
